{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@frozen","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ViewThatFits","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Content","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":"> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Content","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewThatFits"},{"type":"text","text":" evaluates its child views in the order you provide them"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the initializer. It selects the first child whose ideal size on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constrained axes fits within the proposed size. This means that you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provide views in order of preference. Usually this order is largest to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"smallest, but since a view might fit along one constrained axis but not the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other, this isn’t always the case. By default, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewThatFits"},{"type":"text","text":" constrains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in both the horizontal and vertical axes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UploadProgressView"},{"type":"text","text":" that uses "